reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great lil table
reviews.reviewText: We Love this table! Very sturdy & strong feeling. Table was easy to put together, BUT the chairs SUCKED to put together!! We had to take a break & come back after each doing one we were both so frustrated with it. We definitely recommend if ur looking for a nice small kitchen table. Great for the money!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 18, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Really a nice table set for the price, perfect for the small family. Comes up with the manual and easy to assembly. Looks like its gonna be durable for some time as well.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Simple and elegant
reviews.reviewText: We just moved apartment and were looking for a small dining table which could fit in the space. This one fits perfectly, neither too big nor too small. The table is pretty much sturdy and easy to clean. I received the package two days back and assembled it same day. Assembling took may be a couple of hours. The seat cushions were hard to align and each chair perhaps took 10-15 minutes. I liked the rounded corners in the table. If you have small kids then you would truly appreciate that.The chairs look really nice for the price paid for the whole set. Those balance pretty well and hopefully kids would not topple those over. The table top perhaps is veneer so it shines well, and as is the case with any veneer furniture, always use table mats to avoid heat stains. This is a good option if you have a limited space.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Looks like the picture…but
reviews.reviewText: I am pleased with this dinette set. It looks just like the picture. However…putting this thing together was a pain in the kisser. The funny metric tool bit and metric screws were difficult. I was so frustrated. And it felt like it took forever to assemble. My hand was sore afterwards. However, since it is assembled now, I am pleased with the outcome. I was so pleased, I took myself out to eat instead of serving myself a meal on the dinette set. I’ll around to it. Assembly is a pain, but as a final assembled product only, I do recommend. Enjoy!
